androidx.browser.customtabs

Class CustomTabsServiceConnection

  • java.lang.Object
    • androidx.browser.customtabs.CustomTabsServiceConnection

  • public abstract class CustomTabsServiceConnection
extends java.lang.Object
    Abstract ServiceConnection to use while binding to a CustomTabsService. Any client implementing this is responsible for handling changes related with the lifetime of the connection like rebinding on disconnect.

      • onCustomTabsServiceConnected

        public abstract void onCustomTabsServiceConnected(ComponentName name,
                                                  CustomTabsClient client)
        Called when a connection to the CustomTabsService has been established.
        Parameters:
        name - The concrete component name of the service that has been connected.
        client - CustomTabsClient that contains the IBinder with which the connection have been established. All further communication should be initiated using this client.

Generated javadoc for the new package structure to make it clearer which packages are bundled with the Android operating system, and which are packaged with your app's APK. Going forward, the android.* package hierarchy will be reserved for Android packages that ship with the operating system; other packages will be issued in the new androidx.* package hiearchy.
